2500|$|On October 1, 2001, radio {{personality}} and hip-hop activist David [...] "Davey D" [...] Cook was terminated, due {{to what the}} station said were consistently low ratings. His dismissal occurred after new Program Director Michael Martin {{took charge of the}} station, and happened {{at the same time as}} the station changed many programming elements, as well as coinciding with <b>the</b> <b>layoffs</b> of several other station personnel, including on-air personalities Trace-Dog Nunez, Rosary Bides, and Franzen Wong. Cook, however, claims his departure was due to his political views, including his having aired statements from California Congresswoman Barbara Lee and rapper Boots of The Coup voicing opposition to the War in Afghanistan.|$|E
